{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-modules-jsx","path":"/modules/flexible-pathfinding","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"html":"<h1 id=\"flexiblepathfinding\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#flexiblepathfinding\" aria-label=\"flexiblepathfinding permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>FlexiblePathfinding</h1>\n<p>A plugin-based JPS pathfinder for Terasology.</p>\n<p>This is a clone of the <a href=\"https://github.com/kaen/FlexiblePathfinding\">original repository by Kaen</a>.</p>\n<p>See also <a href=\"https://github.com/Terasology/FlexibleMovement\">FlexibleMovement</a>.</p>\n<h1 id=\"usage\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#usage\" aria-label=\"usage permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Usage</h1>\n<p>You probably want to use the nodes in <code class=\"language-text\">FlexibleMovement</code> directly.</p>\n<p>However, if you're not actually moving anything then you can try the <code class=\"language-text\">PathfinderSystem#requestPath</code> method.</p>\n<p>You can see the basic usage example in the\n<a href=\"https://github.com/kaen/FlexiblePathfinding/blob/master/src/test/java/org/terasology/flexiblepathfinding/helpers/JPSTestHelper.java#L99-L116\">unit test helper</a></p>\n<h1 id=\"hacking\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#hacking\" aria-label=\"hacking permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Hacking</h1>\n<p>Check out the unit tests. You can add a new movement type by writing a new JPSPlugin.</p>","timeToRead":1,"excerpt":"FlexiblePathfinding A plugin-based JPS pathfinder for Terasology. This is a clone of the original repository by Kaen. See alsoâ€¦","frontmatter":{"title":"FlexiblePathfinding","cover":{"publicURL":"/ModuleSite/static/528951686128b0b0eeff76c8479748d7/cover.png","childImageSharp":{"gatsbyImageData":{"layout":"constrained","backgroundColor":"#f8f8f8","images":{"fallback":{"src":"/ModuleSite/static/528951686128b0b0eeff76c8479748d7/9e1f0/cover.jpg","srcSet":"/ModuleSite/static/528951686128b0b0eeff76c8479748d7/8dfb2/cover.jpg 480w,\n/ModuleSite/static/528951686128b0b0eeff76c8479748d7/2f986/cover.jpg 960w,\n/ModuleSite/static/528951686128b0b0eeff76c8479748d7/9e1f0/cover.jpg 1920w","sizes":"(min-width: 1920px) 1920px, 100vw"},"sources":[{"srcSet":"/ModuleSite/static/528951686128b0b0eeff76c8479748d7/3fa69/cover.webp 480w,\n/ModuleSite/static/528951686128b0b0eeff76c8479748d7/986c9/cover.webp 960w,\n/ModuleSite/static/528951686128b0b0eeff76c8479748d7/34dc0/cover.webp 1920w","type":"image/webp","sizes":"(min-width: 1920px) 1